### 1.5 MATRIC EXAM-ONLY PATHWAYS (2024 Pricing)

#### **Option A: Amended Senior Certificate (ASC) - BEST for Adults 21+**
- **✅ TRUE EXAM-ONLY** - No SBA requirements
- **Eligibility:** 21+ years, GETC/Grade 9/equivalent
- **Exam:** 100% final examination
- **Cost:** **FREE** through government Second Chance Matric Programme
- **Registration:** Provincial education offices or eservices.gov.za
- **Exam Sessions:** May/June & October/November
- **Subjects:** Same as NSC (choose 7)
- **AI-Learning:** ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Perfect for self-study

#### **Option B: SACAI (Independent Candidate)**
- **Eligibility:** Any age, completed previous SBA OR writing ASC
- **Cost per Subject:** R1,813.75 (standard) | R2,091.77 (practical/language)
- **Estimated Total (7 subjects):** ~R12,000-R14,000
- **Exam Sessions:** May/June & October/November
- **Registration:** Opens January, closes February (May/Jun) | June-July (Oct/Nov)
- **Provider:** sacai.org.za

#### **Option C: IEB (Independent Examinations Board)**
- **Target:** Private school learners OR independents with prior SBA
- **Cost:** R8,605 for 7 subjects package
- **Extra Subjects:** R1,490/subject (8th+)
- **Single Subject:** R1,491
- **May/June Rewrite:** R1,807/subject
- **Advantage:** Highly regarded by universities
- **Provider:** ieb.co.za

#### **Option D: NSC Part-Time (State)**
- **⚠️ Requires Prior SBA Completion**
- **Cost:** FREE through government
- **Use Case:** Improving previous results, completing missing subjects
- **Registration:** October-February (for May/June exams)

---

## PART 2: VOCATIONAL & TECHNICAL EDUCATION

### 2.1 TVET COLLEGES - NC(V) Programs (NQF Levels 2-4)

**Equivalent:** Grade 10-12 alternative  
**Duration:** 3 years (Level 2, 3, 4)  
**Total TVET Colleges:** 50 public colleges, 364+ campuses nationwide  
**AI-Learning Suitability:** ⭐⭐⭐⭐ (Theory components)

#### **Structure - 7 Subjects per Level:**

**Fundamental Subjects (3 - Compulsory):**
1. Language (English/Afrikaans)
2. Mathematics OR Mathematical Literacy
3. Life Orientation

**Vocational Subjects (4 - Field-Specific):**

#### **ENGINEERING PROGRAMS:**

| Field | Vocational Subjects | Career Paths | Exam-Only |
|-------|---------------------|--------------|-----------|
| **Electrical Engineering (Light Current)** | Electrical Technology, Industrial Electronics, Mathematics, Engineering Science | Electrician, Technician | ⚠️ Practicals required |
| **Electrical Engineering (Heavy Current)** | Electrical Technology, Power Systems, Mathematics, Engineering Science | Power Systems, Industrial | ⚠️ Practicals required |
| **Mechanical Engineering** | Mechanotechnology, Engineering Drawing, Mathematics, Engineering Science | Fitter, Turner, Machinist | ⚠️ Practicals required |
| **Civil Engineering** | Civil Technology, Engineering Drawing, Mathematics, Engineering Science | Construction, Surveying | ⚠️ Practicals required |
| **Automotive** | Motor & Diesel Trade Theory, Mathematics, Mechanotechnology, Engineering Drawing | Mechanic, Auto Electrician | ⚠️ Practicals required |

#### **BUSINESS PROGRAMS:**

| Field | Vocational Subjects | Career Paths | Exam-Only |
|-------|---------------------|--------------|-----------|
| **Office Administration** | Office Practice, Computer Practice, Management Communication, Office Data Processing | Admin Assistant, Secretary | ✅ Yes (theory) |
| **Finance, Economics & Accounting** | Financial Accounting, Economics, Management, Entrepreneurship | Bookkeeper, Accountant Assistant | ✅ Yes |
| **Marketing** | Marketing, Sales Management, Computer Practice, Entrepreneurship | Marketing Assistant, Sales | ✅ Yes |
| **Management** | Management, Personnel Management, Labour Relations, Entrepreneurship | Junior Manager, Supervisor | ✅ Yes |
| **Transport & Logistics** | Supply Chain, Transport Economics, Computer Practice, Management | Logistics Coordinator | ✅ Yes |

#### **IT & COMPUTER SCIENCE:**
- Information Technology & Computer Science
- Programming & Robotics (new - select colleges)
- **Subjects:** Programming, Systems Support, Networking, Computer Practice

#### **OTHER FIELDS:**
- **Hospitality:** Food Production, Food & Beverage Service, Accommodation Services, Hospitality Services
- **Tourism:** Tourism Operations, Sustainable Tourism, Customer Care, Computer Practice
- **Primary Agriculture:** Plant Production, Animal Production, Agricultural Management, Agricultural Science
- **Safety in Society:** Public Safety, Security Operations, Criminal Justice, Safety Management
- **Education & Development:** Early Childhood Development, Education Studies

**National N Diploma Requirements:**
- Complete N-Level 2, 3, 4 certificates (21 subjects total)
- **Engineering:** 18-24 months (1800-2400 hours) workplace experience
- **Business/Other:** 18 months workplace experience
- **Exam-Only:** ❌ Workplace experience mandatory for diploma

**Costs:** R2,000-R8,000/year (government subsidized)  
**Exams:** 3 sessions per year (March, June, November)

---

### 2.2 NATED Programs (N1-N6)

**Status:** Legacy system, being phased out but still valid  
**Levels:** N1-N3 (foundational), N4-N6 (advanced)

#### **ENGINEERING STUDIES N4-N6:**

**Core Subjects:**
- Mathematics N4, N5, N6
- Engineering Science N4, N5, N6
- Industrial Electronics N4, N5, N6 (Electrical)
- Mechanotechnology N4, N5, N6 (Mechanical)
- Engineering Drawing N4, N5, N6

**Specializations:**
- Electrical Engineering
- Mechanical Engineering  
- Civil Engineering
- Chemical Engineering
- Instrumentation

**National N Diploma:** N4-N6 + 24 months (2670 hours) practical experience

#### **BUSINESS STUDIES N4-N6:**

**Subjects:**
- Financial Accounting N4-N6
- Entrepreneurship & Business Management N4-N6
- Computer Practice N4-N6
- Management Communication N4-N6
- Marketing Management / Sales Management / Personnel Management N4-N6

**National N Diploma:** N4-N6 + 18 months workplace experience

**Exam Sessions:**
- Engineering: March/April, July/August, November (3x per year)
- Business: June, November (2x per year)

**AI-Learning Suitability:** ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Theory highly suitable  
**Costs:** R3,000-R10,000/year at TVET colleges

---

### 2.3 Trade Tests & Artisan Qualifications

**Governing Body:** QCTO (Quality Council for Trades and Occupations)

**Eligibility Pathways to Trade Test:**
1. N2 Certificate + Trade Theory + 3 years experience
2. N6/National Technical Diploma + 18-36 months experience  
3. NCV Level 3 or 4 + relevant experience
4. Technical Grade 12 + Maths/Science + Trade Theory + 3 years experience
5. Grade 9 + 4 years relevant experience

**Trade Test Components:**
- **Practical Assessment:** Hands-on demonstration of skills
- **Theory Exam:** Technical knowledge
- **Logbook:** Verified workplace experience

**Common Trades:**
- Electrician, Plumber, Welder, Fitter & Turner, Millwright, Boilermaker
- Automotive Mechanic, Diesel Mechanic, Auto Electrician
- Carpenter, Bricklayer, Plasterer, Painter

**Exam-Only:** ❌ Requires practical demonstration + verified experience  
**AI-Learning:** ⭐⭐⭐ Theory preparation, practical skills need training

