## PART 4: PROFESSIONAL CERTIFICATIONS & COUNCIL REGISTRATIONS

### 4.1 ENGINEERING - ECSA

**Council:** Engineering Council of South Africa (ecsa.co.za)

**Professional Categories:**
1. **Professional Engineer (Pr Eng)** - BSc Eng/B.Eng + 3-4 years experience
2. **Professional Technologist (Pr Tech Eng)** - B.Tech/National Diploma + experience
3. **Professional Technician (Pr Techni Eng)** - N6/NCV + experience
4. **Candidate** - During studies/training period

**Registration Process:**
- Accredited engineering qualification
- Supervised workplace experience (logbook)
- Professional review (interview/competency assessment)

**2024 Costs:**
- **Initial Registration:** R1,950 (with candidate history) | R3,900 (without)
- **Annual Fee - Professional:** R5,713 (no exemption) | R4,982 (with IPET membership)
- **Annual Fee - Candidate:** R2,310 (no exemption) | R2,082 (with exemption)

---

### 4.2 ACCOUNTING & FINANCE

#### **SAICA - Chartered Accountant CA(SA)**

**Path:** BCom Accounting → CTA/Postgrad Diploma → Training Contract (3 years) → ITC → APC Exam

**Exams:**
- **ITC** (Initial Test of Competence) - After 18 months articles
- **APC** (Assessment of Professional Competence) - Final qualifying exam

**2024 Costs:**
- **Training Contract Levy:** R3,720.55/year per trainee
- Exam fees included in training program
- **Total to Qualification:** ~R150,000-R200,000 (including degree + articles)

#### **SAIPA - Professional Accountant (SA)**

**Path:** BCom/National Diploma → Training Contract → Competency Exams

**2024 Fees:**
- **Professional Evaluation:** R1,337.54 (Candidate/Trainee)
- **RPL Assessment:** R1,330.55
- **Acc Tech Evaluation:** R2,591.43
- **Annual Membership:** R1,330.55 (Trainee) to R5,289.56 (Practitioner)

#### **CIMA - Chartered Management Accountant**

**Structure:** Certificate → Operational → Management → Strategic

**2024 Costs (ZAR):**
- **Registration:** R3,450 (one-off)
- **Annual Subscription:** R5,050
- **Certificate Exam:** R2,100
- **Operational Objective Test:** R2,450
- **Management Objective Test:** R3,060
- **Strategic Objective Test:** R4,200
- **Strategic Case Study:** R7,150
- **Total to CIMA Qualification:** R60,000-R80,000

---

### 4.3 LEGAL PRACTICE - LPC

**Council:** Legal Practice Council (lpc.org.za)

**Qualification Path:**
1. **LLB Degree** (4 years) - UNISA R80,000-R130,000 total
2. **Articles of Clerkship** - Practical training (usually 2 years) + 400 hours coursework
3. **LPC Attorneys Admission Examination** (4 papers)
4. **High Court Admission** - Application + oath

**LPC Exam 2024:**
- **Paper 1:** Court Procedures (High Court, Magistrates, MVA, Criminal)
- **Paper 2:** Wills & Estates
- **Paper 3:** Professional Ethics & Attorneys' Practice
- **Paper 4:** Legal Practitioners' Bookkeeping

**Exam Details:**
- **Registration Fee:** R345 (for all papers in session)
- **Pass Mark:** 50% | Oral exam if 40-49%
- **Sessions:** 2 per year (March & August)
- **2024 Dates:** March 13-14 | August 21-22

**Post-Admission Costs:**
- LSSA membership
- Fidelity Fund contributions
- Professional indemnity insurance

---

### 4.4 MEDICAL - HPCSA

**Council:** Health Professions Council of SA (hpcsa.co.za)

**Standard Path (SA-qualified):**
1. **MBChB** (5-6 years) - NOT exam-only, clinical training essential
2. **2-Year Internship** - Compulsory supervised practice
3. **1-Year Community Service**
4. **HPCSA Registration**

**Foreign-Qualified Path:**
1. **Curriculum Review** - HPCSA evaluates foreign qualification
2. **Medical Board Examination** (administered by UKZN):
   - Written: 75 clinical items + 25 ethical/legal items
   - Practical: OSCE (Objective Structured Clinical Exam)
   - Max 3 attempts in 2 years
3. **12 Months Supervised Practice** (if passed)
4. **HPCSA Registration**

**Alternative Entry to Medicine:**
- **BSc → Medical Transfer:** Excellent BSc grades → transfer to Year 2/3 MBChB
- **GEMP at Wits:** Graduate Entry Medical Programme - Graduates enter Year 3 (4-year pathway to MBChB)

**Exam-Only:** ❌ Medicine requires extensive clinical training

---

### 4.5 TEACHING - SACE

**Council:** South African Council for Educators (sace.org.za)

**Qualifications Required:**
- **B.Ed** (4 years) - Integrated teaching degree
- **Bachelor's + PGCE** (3+1 years) - Subject degree + teaching qualification

**SACE Registration Requirements:**
1. Completed teaching qualification (certified transcripts)
2. SA ID / Passport + valid work permit
3. Matric certificate
4. Police clearance (<6 months old, SAPS verified)
5. Application form (online via eservices.gov.za)

**2024 Registration Fees:**
- **SA Citizens:** R200
- **Non-SA Citizens:** R400

**Processing Time:** 4-6 weeks

**Non-SA Citizens Additional Requirements:**
- SAQA evaluation of foreign qualifications
- DBE evaluation for employment in education
- Work permit stating "teaching" permission

---

### 4.6 CONSTRUCTION - SACPCMP

**Council:** SA Council for Project & Construction Management Professions

**2024/2025 Fees:**
- **Application Fee:** R300
- **Exam Fee:** R1,100
- **Registration Fee:** R1,180 (Certified) | R1,205 (Professional)
- **Interview Fee (Professional):** R3,800
- **Annual Fee:** R3,350 (Certified) | R3,970 (Professional)

---

## PART 5: ALTERNATIVE PATHWAYS

### 5.1 Recognition of Prior Learning (RPL)

**Purpose:** Formal recognition of skills/knowledge from work, informal learning, life experience

**UNISA RPL Eligibility:**
- **Undergraduate:** 23+ years + 3+ years relevant experience
- **Postgraduate:** 23+ years + 5+ years relevant experience

**Assessment Methods:**
- Portfolio of evidence
- Challenge examinations
- Interviews
- Work-based projects
- Skills demonstrations

**Maximum Credit:** 50% of qualification via RPL

**SAIPA RPL Cost:** R1,330.55  
**Process:** Apply → Assessment → Credit granted → Enroll for remaining modules

**AI-Learning Application:** ✅ Study independently with AI, demonstrate competency via RPL

---

### 5.2 Mature Age Entry (23+)

**Pathway:** University admission without NSC if 23+ with relevant experience

**Requirements:**
- Minimum age 23
- Relevant work experience (3-5 years)
- RPL assessment
- Senate approval

**Best for:** Working professionals seeking formal qualifications

---

### 5.3 SETA/QCTO Occupational Certificates

**Status:** Legacy SETA qualifications → Occupational Certificates (July 2024 transition)

**Structure:**
- Knowledge module (theory)
- Practical skills module
- Work experience module
- **EISA** (External Integrated Summative Assessment)

**21 SETAs covering ALL sectors:**
- Services SETA: Customer service, project management, leadership
- MICT SETA: IT, end-user computing, telecommunications
- ETDP SETA: Assessor, facilitator, moderator training
- MERSETA: Manufacturing, engineering skills
- FoodBev SETA: Food & beverage operations
- CHIETA: Chemical, hygiene, health
- W&RSETA: Wholesale, retail
- BANKSETA: Banking, microfinance
- FASSET: Finance, accounting sectors
- SASSETA: Safety & security

**Exam-Only:** ⚠️ Requires competency demonstration + assessment (not pure exam-only)

**AI-Learning:** ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Excellent for knowledge modules

