### Getting Started - Your Action Plan:

**Step 1:** Determine your starting point
- No matric? → ASC (FREE, age 21+) or SACAI (R12k)
- Have matric? → UNISA degree
- Have degree? → Honours/Masters
- Working professional? → RPL pathway

**Step 2:** Choose your career goal (use Part 8 table)

**Step 3:** Select exam board/institution
- School level: ASC/SACAI/IEB
- Tertiary: UNISA (best exam-only option)
- Professional: Relevant council (ECSA/SAICA/LPC/HPCSA/SACE)

**Step 4:** Set up AI learning environment
- Free: ChatGPT, Gemini, DeepSeek
- Paid: Claude Pro (R350/month), ChatGPT Plus (R330/month)

**Step 5:** Download curriculum/syllabus
- School: education.gov.za (CAPS documents)
- UNISA: Study guides on myUnisa
- Professional: Body websites

**Step 6:** Create study schedule (12-18 months typical for matric, 3-4 years for degree)

**Step 7:** Register for exams
- Matric: 3-6 months before exam session
- UNISA: Semester registration periods
- Professional: Per exam body schedule

**Step 8:** Study with AI + past papers

**Step 9:** Write exams

**Step 10:** Obtain accreditation & launch career!

